eight="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" class="drawer-chevron" data-v-c018db0d><path d="M6 12L10 8L6 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" data-v-c018db0d></path></svg></button></li><li data-v-c018db0d><a href="/about" class="drawer-link" data-v-c018db0d>About</a></li><!--]--></ul><!----></nav></div><!----></aside></div><!--]--></div></div></header><main data-v-26ed1394><!--[--><div><div class="post-wrapper" data-v-29b3eeb5><header class="post-header" data-v-29b3eeb5 data-v-01b90259><div class="post-header__bg" data-v-01b90259><div class="bg-canvas__wrapper white" data-v-01b90259 data-v-6ffb6bc3><canvas data-v-6ffb6bc3></canvas></div></div><div class="post-header__content" data-v-01b90259><div class="post-header__meta label-4" data-v-01b90259>blog • September 19, 2025</div><h1 class="post-header__title title-h1" data-v-01b90259>YMS: Features, Benefits &amp; Innovations</h1><!----></div><figure class="post-header__image-wrapper" data-v-01b90259><div class="post-header__image-container" data-v-01b90259><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" alt="Post Image" data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/2050x1094/d726705fd7/p.webp 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/2050x1094/d726705fd7/p.webp 2x" class="post-header__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/2050x1094/d726705fd7/p.webp" data-v-01b90259></div><!----></figure></header><div class="post-content" data-v-29b3eeb5><div class="author-container post-author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" data-v-29b3eeb5 data-v-dd1fd95f><h2 class="about-the-author" data-v-dd1fd95f>About the Author</h2><div class="author-info" data-v-dd1fd95f><div class="author-metadata" data-v-dd1fd95f><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" alt data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/420x420/2b235317ec/terminal-symbol-black.png 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/420x420/2b235317ec/terminal-symbol-black.png 2x" class="author-avatar" itemprop="image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/420x420/2b235317ec/terminal-symbol-black.png" data-v-dd1fd95f><div class="author-details" data-v-dd1fd95f><p class="author-name" itemprop="name" data-v-dd1fd95f>Terminal Industries Staff</p><p class="author-role" itemprop="jobTitle" data-v-dd1fd95f>Terminal Team</p></div></div><p class="author-bio" itemprop="description" data-v-dd1fd95f>Coming together in collaboration, the staff of Terminal Industries unites diverse expertise in logistics, technology, and operations to deliver forward-thinking insights. As a collective, they are leaders in shaping the future of the yard with innovation and measurable impact. </p></div><a href="/contact" class="author-cta-button button label-4 author-cta-button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);" data-v-dd1fd95f data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[--> Talk to an expert <!--]--></span></a></div><div data-v-29b3eeb5><nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb" data-v-29b3eeb5 data-v-ff0d7e07><ol class="breadcrumbs-list" data-v-ff0d7e07><!--[--><li class="breadcrumbs-item" data-v-ff0d7e07><a href="/resources" class="breadcrumbs-link" data-v-ff0d7e07>Resources</a><span class="breadcrumbs-separator" aria-hidden="true" data-v-ff0d7e07>/</span></li><li class="breadcrumbs-item" data-v-ff0d7e07><a href="/resources/blogs" class="breadcrumbs-link" data-v-ff0d7e07>Blogs</a><span class="breadcrumbs-separator" aria-hidden="true" data-v-ff0d7e07>/</span></li><li class="breadcrumbs-item" data-v-ff0d7e07><span class="breadcrumbs-current" aria-current="page" data-v-ff0d7e07>YMS: Features, Benefits &amp; Innovations</span><!----></li><!--]--></ol></nav><div id="summarize-button" class="summarize-button" style="padding-bottom:16px;" data-v-29b3eeb5></div><div class="post-content-wrapper post-content-body" data-v-29b3eeb5 data-v-1c7eea09><div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-3xl prose-headings:font-medium prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-p:text-gray-600 prose-a:text-green-700 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline prose-strong:font-semibold prose-img:rounded-lg prose-hr:border-gray-200" data-v-1c7eea09><!--[--><h1 id="yms-transforming-yard-operations-in-modern-logistics" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>YMS: Transforming Yard Operations in Modern Logistics</h1><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Yard Management Software (YMS)</strong><span style="color: " data-v-1c7eea09> is a crucial technology solution that connects warehouse management systems and transportation networks. While warehouses and highways have seen significant digital adva</span>ncements, the yard still remains mostly untouched by technology in the logistics world.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>You are under increasing pressure to optimize operations as <strong data-v-1c7eea09>over $50 billion worth of goods</strong> are transported daily through more than 50,000 warehouses and factories across North America. Traditional methods of managing yards often lead to bottlenecks that affect entire supply chains, resulting in delays, higher costs, and decreased efficiency. YMS tackles these issues by offering real-time visibility, automated processes, and intelligent resource allocation within yard operations.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>This detailed guide delves into the key features and transformative advantages of implementing YMS in your supply chain operations. You&#39;ll discover how cutting-edge solutions are reshaping yard digitization, explore emerging trends in automation and AI integration, and gain insights into Terminal Industries&#39; groundbreaking <strong data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal </strong><strong data-v-1c7eea09><span style="color: #000000" data-v-1c7eea09>Industries </span></strong><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Yard Operating System™</strong> that&#39;s setting new standards for yard execution platforms.</p><h2 id="the-role-of-yard-management-in-modern-supply-chains" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>The Role of Yard Management in Modern Supply Chains</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Yards are the crucial link between warehouse operations and transportation networks. Every day, goods worth over $50 billion move through more than 50,000 warehouses and factories in North America. Yards play a vital role in supply chain logistics by coordinating the movement of freight, trailers, containers, and other assets.</p><h3 id="the-challenges-of-traditional-yard-management" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>The Challenges of Traditional Yard Management</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Traditional yard management methods present significant logistical problems that affect the entire supply chain. These environments are primarily driven by manual processes, where yard personnel depend on clipboards, radios, and visual inspections to monitor asset locations and organize movements. As a result, drivers often waste time looking for parking spots or waiting at dock doors without any clear information about availability.</p><h4 id="how-operational-inefficiencies-create-supply-chain-bottlenecks" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>How Operational Inefficiencies Create Supply Chain Bottlenecks</h4><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>These operational inefficiencies lead to supply chain bottlenecks that increase costs and delays throughout the network:</p><ul data-v-1c7eea09><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Managers have no real-time visibility into trailer locations and status due to asset visibility gaps.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Lengthy queues and driver detention fees are caused by manual check-in processes.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Up to 30% reduction in throughput capacity is caused by inefficient dock door utilization.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Poor communication systems exist between yard staff, drivers, and warehouse teams.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Unnecessary asset movements and congestion occur due to suboptimal parking assignments.</p></li></ul><h3 id="the-far-reaching-effects-of-inefficiencies" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>The Far-Reaching Effects of Inefficiencies</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The negative effects of these inefficiencies go beyond just the yard area. Delayed shipments can lead to unhappy customers, while increased driver detention fees and longer wait times raise operational costs. With logistics systems facing high demand and a 10% annual growth rate in square footage but a stagnant working-age population, these traditional methods are becoming less sustainable.</p><h3 id="the-need-for-modern-solutions" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>The Need for Modern Solutions</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Modern supply chains require accuracy, speed, and visibility—qualities that manual yard operations cannot provide on a large scale.</p><h2 id="understanding-yard-management-software-yms" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Understanding Yard Management Software (YMS)</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Yard Management Software (YMS) is a specialized technology platform designed to manage and improve the complex operations that take place within logistics yards. It acts as a central hub, turning disorganized yard environments into efficient, data-driven operations. With YMS, you have complete control over every asset, trailer, and movement occurring within your facility.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The main functions of YMS are built around three key areas that address the operational challenges faced by traditional yard management:</p><h3 id="1-real-time-visibility-and-tracking" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>1. Real-Time Visibility and Tracking</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Modern YMS features provide extensive visibility into yard activities through advanced tracking capabilities. You can keep an eye on where trailers are located, which dock doors are assigned, and how drivers are checking in and out—all in real-time. This level of visibility eliminates the uncertainty that often comes with manual yard operations, giving you accurate information about where your assets are and their current status. Such real-time visibility plays a crucial role in improving last-mile logistics.</p><h3 id="2-resource-optimization" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>2. Resource Optimization</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>One of the critical abilities of YMS is smart resource allocation, which helps you run your operations more efficiently. The software intelligently manages which dock doors are being used, optimizes how parking spots are utilized, and coordinates spotter movements based on priority levels and operational constraints. This means you&#39;ll benefit from automated decision-making that takes multiple factors into account at once—something that&#39;s difficult to do manually. Furthermore, with the integration of IoT technologies, resource optimization can be taken to an entirely new level.</p><h3 id="3-system-integration-capabilities" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>3. System Integration Capabilities</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>YMS platforms excel at connecting different systems together, specifically Warehouse Management Systems (WMS) and Transportation Management Systems (TMS). This integration allows for a smooth flow of data between these systems, ensuring that inbound and outbound operations are synchronized. As a result, warehouse teams will always know when trailers are arriving, and transportation coordinators will be aware of dock availability.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Advanced YMS solutions stand out from the rest by using AI-powered automation, computer vision technology, and customizable workflow engines. These features allow you to tailor your operations based on specific business rules while still being able to scale across multiple facility locations. The most advanced platforms even use machine learning algorithms to continuously improve yard operations based on past patterns and real-time conditions.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>In addition to these functionalities, implementing a robust YMS can also greatly enhance your overall supply chain management, making it more streamlined and efficient.</p><h2 id="key-benefits-of-implementing-yms-in-modern-supply-chains" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Key Benefits of Implementing YMS in Modern Supply Chains</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The implementation of <strong data-v-1c7eea09>YMS benefits</strong> extends far beyond simple operational improvements, creating measurable impacts across multiple dimensions of supply chain efficiency. Organizations deploying advanced <strong data-v-1c7eea09>yms</strong> solutions consistently report dramatic improvements in their core operational metrics.</p><h3 id="increased-throughput-and-faster-turnaround-times" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Increased Throughput and Faster Turnaround Times</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Modern yard management systems optimize every aspect of yard processes, from trailer arrival to departure. You can expect <strong data-v-1c7eea09>throughput improvements of 50% or more</strong> when implementing AI-powered solutions that automate gate processes and orchestrate yard activities. These systems eliminate bottlenecks by intelligently routing assets, predicting dock availability, and coordinating with warehouse operations to minimize wait times.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The automation of check-in and check-out processes reduces driver detention fees by up to <strong data-v-1c7eea09>12%</strong>, while intelligent scheduling ensures optimal resource allocation throughout peak and off-peak periods.</p><h3 id="enhanced-asset-utilization-and-reduced-congestion" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Enhanced Asset Utilization and Reduced Congestion</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Strategic parking assignments based on load attributes and delivery schedules maximize yard space efficiency. Advanced <strong data-v-1c7eea09>YMS</strong> platforms reduce asset search time by <strong data-v-1c7eea09>90%</strong> through real-time tracking and automated location management. You gain complete visibility into trailer locations, contents, and status, enabling proactive decision-making that prevents congestion before it occurs.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Smart dock door management ensures optimal utilization of loading bays, while predictive analytics help you anticipate capacity constraints and adjust operations accordingly.</p><h3 id="improved-safety-and-regulatory-compliance" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Improved Safety and Regulatory Compliance</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Automated monitoring systems continuously track yard activities, ensuring compliance with safety protocols and regulatory standards. Computer vision technology should provide <strong data-v-1c7eea09>99%+ data accuracy</strong> in monitoring vehicle movements, detecting unauthorized access, and identifying potential safety hazards in real-time.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>These systems maintain comprehensive audit trails, simplify regulatory reporting, and reduce liability risks through proactive safety management and incident prevention capabilities. Furthermore, the integration of AI in these processes is proving invaluable in streamlining supply chain regulatory compliance, enhancing overall operational efficiency.</p><h2 id="terminal-industries-innovative-approach-to-yard-digitization" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal Industries&#39; Innovative Approach to Yard Digitization</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal Industries has developed a revolutionary solution to address the critical gap in yard digitization through their proprietary <strong data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal Yard Operating System™ (YOS)</strong>. This AI-native platform represents a fundamental shift from traditional yard management approaches, offering an end-to-end execution platform that bridges the operational and data gaps between highway and warehouse systems.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The <strong data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal Yard Operating System</strong> combines multiple cutting-edge technologies into a unified, scalable solution. At its core lies proprietary AI vision technology that delivers 99.5% data accuracy through computer vision capabilities. This technology enables real-time visibility and automated decision-making processes that were previously impossible with manual yard operations.</p><h3 id="core-technology-components" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Core Technology Components</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal&#39;s platform integrates several advanced technological elements:</p><ul data-v-1c7eea09><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>AI Vision Technology</strong>: Computer vision systems that provide continuous monitoring and data collection across all yard activities</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Data Lakes</strong>: Comprehensive analytics infrastructure that processes vast amounts of operational data for intelligent decision-making</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>SmartYard YMS™</strong>: AI and computer vision-powered workflows that automate gate processes and orchestrate yard activities</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Advanced Yard Solutions</strong>: Specialized applications for ISR compliance, security monitoring, and damage detection</p></li></ul><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The <strong data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal Yard Operating System</strong><sup data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>TM</strong></sup> architecture enables rapid deployment through their Terminal-in-a-Camera™ hardware kit, which can be installed in hours without requiring trenching or extensive infrastructure modifications. This modular, plug-and-play approach allows organizations to implement yard digitization with minimal IT overhead and operational disruption.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Terminal&#39;s solution delivers measurable results, including 50%+ throughput improvements through SmartYard™ automation and 90% reduction in asset search time. The platform&#39;s cloud-native design ensures scalability across multiple yard locations while providing single-pane-of-glass visibility for comprehensive network management.</p><h2 id="overcoming-barriers-to-yard-technology-adoption" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Overcoming Barriers to Yard Technology Adoption</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Yard tech challenges</strong> present significant hurdles for organizations seeking to modernize their operations. You&#39;ll encounter resistance from employees who have relied on manual processes for years, viewing technology as a threat to their established routines and job security. This human element represents one of the most complex aspects of <strong data-v-1c7eea09>change management logistics</strong>.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Legacy system compatibility creates another substantial barrier. Your existing WMS and TMS investments may seem incompatible with new yard management solutions, leading to concerns about data silos and integration costs. Many organizations worry about disrupting current operations during implementation phases.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Budget constraints</strong> often limit technology adoption, particularly when decision-makers struggle to quantify ROI from yard digitization. You might face skepticism from leadership who view yard operations as secondary to warehouse or transportation investments.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Technical infrastructure limitations</strong> compound these challenges. Inadequate lighting, power supply issues, or connectivity problems can make advanced solutions like AI vision technology seem impractical. Your IT teams may lack experience with yard-specific technologies, creating implementation anxiety.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Training and skill gaps</strong> represent another significant obstacle. Your workforce may require extensive education on new systems, creating temporary productivity dips that concern operational managers. The learning curve associated with sophisticated platforms can feel overwhelming.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Modern solutions address these barriers through <strong data-v-1c7eea09>plug-and-play deployment models</strong> that minimize disruption. Terminal&#39;s approach eliminates trenching requirements and reduces IT complexity, while flexible integration layers ensure seamless connectivity with existing systems. Rapid deployment timelines and proven ROI models help overcome budget hesitations, making yard digitization more accessible than traditional implementations suggested.</p><h2 id="future-trends-shaping-yard-management-technology" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Future Trends Shaping Yard Management Technology</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The <strong data-v-1c7eea09>future of yard management</strong> is being transformed by advanced technologies that promise to change how logistics operations work. The most significant advancement is AI in logistics yards, which uses machine learning algorithms for predictive analytics. This allows us to forecast busy periods, allocate resources efficiently, and prevent bottlenecks before they happen.</p><h3 id="1-robotics-integration" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>1. Robotics Integration</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Robotics integration is improving operational efficiency in yard environments. Here&#39;s how:</p><ul data-v-1c7eea09><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Autonomous yard trucks and robotic spotters are taking over manual positioning tasks.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Automated guided vehicles (AGVs) are handling trailer movements with precision that human operators can&#39;t match.</p></li></ul><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>These systems will be working around the clock, increasing productivity while lowering labor costs and safety incidents.</p><h3 id="2-decision-intelligence-capabilities" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>2. Decision Intelligence Capabilities</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Decision intelligence capabilities</strong> powered by machine learning are creating self-optimizing yards that learn from historical patterns and real-time data. These systems analyze thousands of variables simultaneously - from weather conditions to driver schedules - making split-second decisions that maximize efficiency. Advanced <strong data-v-1c7eea09>YMS</strong> platforms now incorporate computer vision technology that provides near-perfect data accuracy, enabling automated processes that were previously impossible.</p><h3 id="3-hyper-connected-yard-ecosystems" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>3. Hyper-Connected Yard Ecosystems</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The combination of IoT sensors, edge computing, and cloud infrastructure is forming highly connected yard ecosystems. Here&#39;s what you can expect:</p><ul data-v-1c7eea09><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>Smart cameras with AI vision technology can detect damage, verify compliance, and track assets without human involvement.</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09>These systems work smoothly with existing WMS and TMS platforms, creating unified data lakes that drive intelligent automation.</p></li></ul><h3 id="4-predictive-maintenance-algorithms" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>4. Predictive Maintenance Algorithms</h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>Predictive maintenance algorithms are extending equipment lifecycles by identifying potential failures before they occur. You can expect reduced downtime and optimized maintenance schedules that align with operational demands rather than arbitrary time intervals.</p><h2 id="conclusion" class="heading-anchor" data-v-1c7eea09>Conclusion</h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The <strong data-v-1c7eea09>yard transformation</strong> revolution is a critical turning point for modern supply chains. Organizations that embrace advanced YMS platforms position themselves at the forefront of <strong data-v-1c7eea09>logistics innovation</strong>, gaining competitive advantages through enhanced visibility, automated processes, and data-driven decision making.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>You cannot afford to let your yard remain a technological black hole while the rest of your supply chain operates with cutting-edge systems. The gap between highway and warehouse digitization demands immediate attention, and the right <strong data-v-1c7eea09>YMS</strong> solution bridges this operational bottleneck effectively.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The Terminal Yard Operating System™ exemplifies the next generation of yard digitization technology. Our AI-native platform delivers:</p><ul data-v-1c7eea09><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Rapid ROI</strong> in under 5 months</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>99.5% data accuracy</strong> through proprietary computer vision</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>50%+ throughput improvements</strong> via SmartYard™ YMS automation</p></li><li data-v-1c7eea09><p data-v-1c7eea09><strong data-v-1c7eea09>Scalable deployment</strong> across yard networks</p></li></ul><p style="text-align: left;" data-v-1c7eea09>The logistics landscape continues evolving at breakneck speed. Your yard operations must evolve alongside these changes to maintain operational excellence and customer satisfaction. Consider exploring Terminal Industries&#39; innovative approach to yard digitization as you plan your next strategic technology investment.</p><!--]--></div><div class="tag-button-list mt-8" data-v-1c7eea09 data-v-95826a6e><!--[--><button class="tag-button button label-4 tag-button" style="width:fit-content;" data-v-95826a6e data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->ai<!--]--></span></button><button class="tag-button button label-4 tag-button" style="width:fit-content;" data-v-95826a6e data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->automation in operations<!--]--></span></button><button class="tag-button button label-4 tag-button" style="width:fit-content;" data-v-95826a6e data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->efficiency <!--]--></span></button><button class="tag-button button label-4 tag-button" style="width:fit-content;" data-v-95826a6e data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Logistics Technology <!--]--></span></button><button class="tag-button button label-4 tag-button" style="width:fit-content;" data-v-95826a6e data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->technology<!--]--></span></button><!--]--></div><div class="post-actions" data-v-1c7eea09><!--[--><!--[--><!--[--><button class="ds-button button label-4 ds-button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:rgba(5, 36, 